[[include component:image-block name=https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/theme%3Arevised-ijamea-theme/IJAMEA2.png|caption=Image Sample|width=100px]]

Since [[[component:ijamea-theme|the theme]]] created by [[*user Dr Solo]] has been deleted, this theme used in JP is now available for use in EN.

"局査調例事常異國帝本日大" is the Japanese notation for "Imperial Japanese Anomalous Matters Examination Agency". It's written from right to left and by a traditional form of kanji used in Japan before WW II.
And this logo was created by [[*user Nanimono Demonai]], I borrowed it from [*https://scp-jp.wikidot.com/foundation-or-goi-logo his artwork in JP]. Of course, it can be used under CC BY-SA 3.0. This logo is modeled on the letter "異" in [*https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seal_script ancient seal script] and a butterfly(蝶/chō), which is pronounced the same as "調" in Japanese. "異調" stands for "**異**常事例**調**査局(AMEA)". 

[[/tab]]
